    "body": "yup. the lame thing about that is you couldn't for example do:\n\n``` js\napp.use('/api', myapierrorhandlerhere)\n```\n\nwhich would provide proper status codes and more information/content-negotiation whereas the main app error handler might just 500 everything other than 404 and show some page, it just ruins the flexibility a bit, plus then there is no \"next\" middleware so next(err) stops even remotely making sense\n",
